job.title: Delhi University Asst, Technician & Other Recruitment 2021 – Apply Online for 1145 Posts
job.body:
Total Vacancies:1145

 

Description:

The National Testing Agency issued a total of 1145 for the posts of Junior Assistant. The online application for the posts of Junior Assistant under the National Testing Agency shall start from 23-02-2021. The eligible candidates must submit the online application before 28-04-2021. Check the complete details below so that all the doubts about the filling of the online application get cleared. For more such updates do visit theprograd.com.The ProGrad jobs.

 

Mode of application & application fee:

The mode of application is online and after filling in the required details you have to provide the billing details for the application fee.

  • The application fee for the OBC / EWS is 800/-
  • The application fee for SC / ST / PH is 600/-
  • The application fee for General is 1000-
  • For more details, you can refer to the notification. The link is given at the bottom.

Important dates:

  • The Starting date to apply for this online application form is 23-02-2021
  • The Last date to apply for this online application form is 28-04-2021
  • Last Date for Payment of Fee: 29-04-2021 (Extended from 17-03-2021 to 29-04-2021) up to 23:50 Hrs
  • Date for Correction of Application Form: 30-04 to 02-05-2021 (Only for Addl Applicants between 31-03 to 28-04-2021)
  • Date for Download Admit Card: To be announced later through the website
  • Date for Exam: To be announced later through the website
  • Centre, Date & Shift the Exam: To be announced later through the website
  • Date for Display of Recorded Responses & Answer Key: To be announced later through the website

Educational qualification required:

To apply for the posts issued by the National Testing Agency you must have fallen in the educational criteria given below:

  • You must have a degree in civil (Engg) to apply for the post of Junior Assistant

Age limit criteria:

To apply for this job you must have fallen in the age limit criteria provided by the National Testing Agency:

  • No information about Age limit criteria
  • For age relaxation criteria you can refer to the notification given below in The ProGrad jobs.\

Pay Scale:

The pay scale as per 7th pay commission for the post of Junior Assistant is:

  • As per norms
  • Check the detailed notification also if we missed something

Detailed vacancies:

The vacancies in detail are given below. Check below that National Testing Agency issued this notification for which posts.

How to apply for NTA Delhi University?

  • First, visit the official website.
  • Register yourself on the portal of the National Testing Agency.
  • Login yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification of Junior Assistant.
  • Fill up the complete details that are asked in the application form.
  • Upload your photo and signature with the dimensions asked in the instructions.
  • Submit the application fee
  • Finally, download the application form for future needs.
  • If already register then, login here

Download official notification
